## ADDING NEW MODES

To add a mode to this directory:

1. Write the mode file in `modes/` with TRIGGER CONDITIONS (positive and negative), EPISTEMOLOGICAL POSTURE, DEFAULT GEAR, and RAG PROFILE sections.
2. Add an entry to this directory with: intent category, positive triggers, negative triggers, key signal, and 3 example anchors (✓) + 2-3 counter-examples (✗).
3. Add boundary pairs to the disambiguation table for any existing modes that share semantic territory with the new mode.
4. Add the new mode to the Intent-to-Mode Map under the appropriate category.

The discrimination quality improves as modes are added — more boundary pairs means more explicit routing rules.
